Migration data of Mexico, from 1970 to 2050 aggregated by ages.

Source: R/data.R
df_migration.Rd

A dataset containing the estimated migration by CONAPO between 1970 and 2050. These estimations are disaggregated by year, state, sex and type of migration (immigration or emigration). This dataset includes emigration rate estimates. This dataset groups the information by groups of ages that increases by 5 years.

Usage

df_migration

Format

A data frame with 84,672 rows and 8 variables:

year

Year of the data

state

State where the migration occurred

CVE_GEO

Geographical code of the state of occurrence

sex

Sex of the migrants

age_group

Age group to which belongs the data

type

Type of migration: Interstate, International or Total

emigrants

Number of emigrants

immigrants

Number of immigrants

migratoin

Net migration (immigrants - emigrants)

em_rate

emigration rate

im_rate

immigration rate
